wanUseTrunkGroups.name: wanUseTrunkGroups

wanLineEntry.name: wanLineEntry
wanLineEntry.description: An entry in the wan line table.

wanLineIfIndex.name: wanLineIfIndex
wanLineIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex from the Interfaces table of MIB II (RFC 1213).

wanLineName.name: wanLineName
wanLineName.description: A textual name of the wanLine as assigned through the menu sytem.

wanLineChannels.name: wanLineChannels
wanLineChannels.description: The number of ds0 channels supported.

wanLineStateString.name: wanLineStateString
wanLineStateString.description: A textual representation of the wanLineState as displayed by the menu sytem.

wanLineActiveChannels.name: wanLineActiveChannels
wanLineActiveChannels.description: The number of switched DS0 channels of the line. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-switched-channel(3) and with any following wanLineChannelState bs-clear-pending(8), bs-dialing(9), bs-ringing(10),and bs-connected(11) for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineUsage.name: wanLineUsage
wanLineUsage.description: The usage of the line. SETting values are supported only for T1/E1 links. Only lu-disabled(3), lu-trunk(5), and lu-quiesced(6) for T1/PRI are currently supported for SETs.

wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber1.name: wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber1
wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber1.description: The hunt group phone number associated with the line. This entry is manually entered in the line configurations options.

wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber2.name: wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber2
wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber2.description: The hunt group phone number associated with the line. This entry is manually entered in the line configurations options.

wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber3.name: wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber3
wanLineHuntGrpPhoneNumber3.description: The hunt group phone number associated with the line. This entry is manually entered in the line configurations options.

wanLineAvailableChannels.name: wanLineAvailableChannels
wanLineAvailableChannels.description: The number of DS0 channels of the line configured as Switched and available for making or accepting calls. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels with the wanLineChannelState of bs-idle(7) for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineSwitchedChannels.name: wanLineSwitchedChannels
wanLineSwitchedChannels.description: The number of DS0 channels of the line configured as switched. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-switched-channel(3) and with wanLineChannelState not bs-disabled(18) for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineDisabledChannels.name: wanLineDisabledChannels
wanLineDisabledChannels.description: The number of disabled DS0 channels of the line. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels with the wanLineChannelState of bs-disabled(18) and with any wanLineChannelUsage for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineNailedChannels.name: wanLineNailedChannels
wanLineNailedChannels.description: The number of DS0 channels of the line configured as nailed. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-clear-64(5) and with wanLineChannelState not bs-disabled(18) for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineOutOfServiceChannels.name: wanLineOutOfServiceChannels
wanLineOutOfServiceChannels.description: The number of out-of-service DS0 channels of the line. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-switched-channel and wanLineChannelState of bs-unavailable(2), bs-out-of-service(4), bs-maintenance(16) for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineNet2NetChannels.name: wanLineNet2NetChannels
wanLineNet2NetChannels.description: The number of NET2NET DS0 channels of the line. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-switched-channel and wanLineChannelState of bs-net2net-dialing, bs-net2net-ringing and bs-net2net-connected for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineDtptChannels.name: wanLineDtptChannels
wanLineDtptChannels.description: The number of DTPT DS0 channels of the line. This variable counts the number of wanLineChannels on an enabled line with the wanLineChannelUsage of ds0-switched-channel and wanLineChannelState of bs-dtpt-dialing, bs-dtpt-ringing and bs-dtpt-connected for all the entries in its wanLineChannelEntry table.

wanLineChannelEntry.name: wanLineChannelEntry
wanLineChannelEntry.description: An entry in the wan line table.

wanLineChannelIfIndex.name: wanLineChannelIfIndex
wanLineChannelIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex from the Interfaces table of MIB II (RFC 1213).

wanLineChannelIndex.name: wanLineChannelIndex
wanLineChannelIndex.description: The ds0 channel number with the line.

wanLineChannelState.name: wanLineChannelState
wanLineChannelState.description: The state of the ds0 channel.

wanLineChannelStateString.name: wanLineChannelStateString
wanLineChannelStateString.description: A textual representation of the wanLineChannelState as displayed by the menu sytem.

wanLineChannelErrorCount.name: wanLineChannelErrorCount
wanLineChannelErrorCount.description: The error count encountered on the channel.

wanLineChannelUsage.name: wanLineChannelUsage
wanLineChannelUsage.description: The usage for this ds0 channel.

wanLineChannelTrunkGroup.name: wanLineChannelTrunkGroup
wanLineChannelTrunkGroup.description: The trunk group assigned to this channel. Note: This attribute returns 0 if wanUseTrunkGroup is set to do-not-use(1).

wanLineChannelPhoneNumber.name: wanLineChannelPhoneNumber
wanLineChannelPhoneNumber.description: The phone number of this channel. This is the number sent to the far end in an inverse multiplexed call when instructing the far end to add more bandwidth. The number should contain the minimum number of digits to identify the channel. If the channel is part of a hunt group, the phone number should be blank.

wanLineChannelSlot.name: wanLineChannelSlot
wanLineChannelSlot.description: A slot number for routing incoming calls associated with the channel. A slot-port number zero means calls arriving on this channel can be routed to any port.

wanLineChannelPort.name: wanLineChannelPort
wanLineChannelPort.description: A port number for routing incoming calls associated with the channel. A slot-port number zero means calls arriving on this channel can be routed to any port.

wanLineChannelNailedState.name: wanLineChannelNailedState
wanLineChannelNailedState.description: The nailed group associated with the channel.

wanAvailableChannels.name: wanAvailableChannels
wanAvailableChannels.description: The sum of wanLineAvailableChannels for all lines.

wanSwitchedChannels.name: wanSwitchedChannels
wanSwitchedChannels.description: The sum of wanLineSwitchedChannels for all lines.

wanDisabledChannels.name: wanDisabledChannels
wanDisabledChannels.description: The sum of wanLineDisabledChannels for all lines.

wanActiveChannels.name: wanActiveChannels
wanActiveChannels.description: The sum of wanLineActiveChannels for all lines.

wanNailedChannels.name: wanNailedChannels
wanNailedChannels.description: The sum of wanLineNailedChannels for all lines.

wanOutOfServiceChannels.name: wanOutOfServiceChannels
wanOutOfServiceChannels.description: The sum of wanLineOutOfChannels for all lines.

wanLineChannelUsageTable.name: wanLineChannelUsageTable
wanLineChannelUsageTable.description: Table of channel state summaries per line type.

wanLineChannelUsageEntry.name: wanLineChannelUsageEntry
wanLineChannelUsageEntry.description: An entry in the channel state summary table for the given wanLineUsage and wanLineChannelState.

wanLineChannelUsageCount.name: wanLineChannelUsageCount
wanLineChannelUsageCount.description: The count of channels in the selected wanLineChannelState for the selected wanLineUsage.
